description.narrative: During the COVID-19 pandemic, UNICEF ramped up support to the Government of Tanzania to facilitate access to HIV services among children, adolescents, and pregnant women living with HIV, including the roll-out of more efficacious ART regimens, resulting in 90 percent of children on ART receiving efficacious regimens.;UNICEF supported the establishment of community-based and facility-linked HIV treatment and care interventions for children and adolescents in all planned 18 ;districts. With WHO and UNICEF support, the Ministry of Health introduced a new family-centered model for HIV care and treatment, including linkages to primary health services for children living with HIV. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:17/12/2021
